HEADWORD: Alienee
<hw>Al"ien*ee"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>One to whom the title of property is transferred; -- opposed to
<inv>alienor</inv>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It the <qex>alienee</qex> enters and keeps possession.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alienism</ent>⟦br⟧
